column5: Transcript
alright so it’s a wile e. coyote and roadrunner cartoon
you see them flying down the road
and it stops
it says road runner and something in their little made up Latin
like speediculis incrediblis
and then goes wile e. coyote and something else made up in Latin
and they slowly speed back up again
so they’re running at the speed they were
and then coyote goes to dive on him
with the fork and knife that he has in his hands
but the roadrunner just takes off
and he just hits the ground
so he decides to come up with a plan
he’ll take a boxing glove
put a spring in it put the other end of the spring on a rock
pulls the boxing glove back against the rock
and clips it to the rock
so it won’t fly out till he’s ready
and stands behind the rock
waits to hear the roadrunner coming
lets go of the clip so it will fly out
the boxing glove stays where it is and the rock shoots back
shoots him against the wall so he’s pushed between the wall and the rock
then he looks all panicked
because you see the boxing glove is flying back
and punches him in the face
so instead he decides to get a tightrope
put the tightrope between two cliffs
and walk out with an anvil
and drop it on the uh roadrunner
he’s got a little blueprint plans and everything
so he does it
but as soon as he steps on the tightrope
it stretches right down to the bottom
because of the weight of the anvil
so the roadrunner comes up
does his little BEEP BEEP
flies away
he throws down the anvil
and gets shshot up in the air by the tightrope
but he looks confident
because he’s got a parachute
or he thinks
because he pulls the cord on it
and just craps falls out like an axe a bowl
and a spoon and a plate and a banana
so as he’s falling down
now he looks panicked
he takes out his aspirin
opens it up
you know flying in the air
grabs like two or three out of the air
eats them
and waves goodbye to the camera
as he flies down hits the ground
there’s the little like mushroom cloud of dust
so this time the roadrunner runs into thee
wild cactus mine coyote chases after him
runs into the mine but quickly it gets too dark
so he runs back to the beginning
grabs a little miner’s cap with the ha light on it
so he turns on his light’s red
the roadrunner runs up
his light’s green
so they run away
and they cut to this sort of generic map view
where it’s just the tunnels on a map
and you just see their lights green and red
so they’re running around and roadrunner gets in an elevator
the coyote chases after him
they’re running in a circle
they’re going across up a uh ladder across down a ladder
they do that for a while
the roadrunner jumps off midway of a ladder goes toward another path
but the coyote doesn’t see that
he’s still running around in circle running around in circle
then notices follows him
the roadrunner makes a jump
the coyote just barely makes the jump
he doesn’t quite make it
he has to pull himself up to the other cliff
then they’re go running in this sort of saw blade path
the roadrunner is doing it fine
the coyote is going up down up down up down up down
but the coyote falls a little behind
the roadrunner goes up at the end because it splits
but instead of going on the up path the coyote goes in the straight path
but he’s so used to running up and down and up and down
that he’s apparently still bouncing up and down and up and down
and he’s hitting the ceiling and the floor the ceiling and the floor the ceiling and the floor
and breaks his head not his head his hat
so the light doesn’t work and he’s in pitch black
so he lights a match
and he’s looking around
and he’s in a room full of dynamite
and it cuts to the surface
you hear the explosion
all the cactuses fly up in the air
land down and they all say YIKES
